{"id":480538,"retrievedAt":"2025-04-25T22:00:52.010Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[],"homepage":"","id":480538,"imdb_id":"tt6861410","origin_country":["US","CA"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"The Politics of Perception","overview":"Following an introduction which establishes the social context of the film, ‘The Politics of Perception’ presents a one-minute promotional film advertising a popular Hollywood thriller. This section then repeats itself: a print is generated from the one-minute segment, then a print from the print, and so on as the image and sound slowly disintegrate with each new cycle, until the visual and sound information have completely evolved to white light and white noise. The most original film from the Northwest area. ‘The Politics of Perception’ explores conceptually the paradoxes of communication and the very nature of film itself, progressing from movie reality to its utter abstraction. A maddeningly stimulating work!","popularity":0.0825,"poster_path":"/mhRvbkdZvGm47wDqMmgx3JepESq.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"CA","name":"Canada"}],"release_date":"1973-10-10","revenue":0,"runtime":30,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"English","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"The Politics of Perception","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[],"crew":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":69366,"known_for_department":"Camera","name":"Kirk Tougas","original_name":"Kirk Tougas","popularity":0.154,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"59dcf768c3a36861df081bfc","department":"Directing","job":"Director"},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":69366,"known_for_department":"Camera","name":"Kirk Tougas","original_name":"Kirk Tougas","popularity":0.154,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"59dcf77292514124cd07a398","department":"Editing","job":"Editor"}]},"external_id